         <entry xml:id="aporiyya-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#apopalsamon-dlgenr"
                next="#apisteqiteh-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אפורייא</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾpwryyʾ</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">aporiyyaʾ</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>"
         <gram type="gen" opt="false">m.</gram>
                  <gram type="num" opt="false">pl.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">איפורייאה</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾypwryh</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">iporiyyah</pron>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אמפורייה</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Ox1 Ox2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">איפוריא הטריח</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="K V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">איפוריא</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="Vat2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">איפורייה</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="aporiya-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">plants</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">core borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="frequency" opt="false"/>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false"/>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>summer-fruits</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Ancient Greek+</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>ὀπώρα</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
                     תדע לך שכן שהלך בשעת הקציר כשעת ביכור כל מיני איפורייאה ולא הביא דבר אלא שהוא מן המובקר
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">72,2</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 837: 3</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>
                        The proof is that he went at harvest time, when all kinds of summer-fruits ripen, yet he took only what was ownerless. (Cf. Freedman / Simon II 662)
            </quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">=
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 129 [38d: 38]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">איפוריא</term>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">LeqT Gen 30,14 [76b]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">איפורה</term>)
         </note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Ancient Greek+</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                     <ref target="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/morph?l=o%29pw%2Fr-a&amp;la=greek&amp;can=o%29pw%2Fr-a0"
                          type="entry">ὀπώρα, II.</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">
               Parallels in Yalq und LeqT are taken from GenR. This form only in GenR (Vat 1 corr.). Cf. 
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 239a</bibl>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 138b</bibl>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow 101a</bibl> (Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ὀπωριαῖα</term>) “fruit”. Other spellings: <term xml:lang="jpa">איפורה</term>, <term xml:lang="jpa">איפוריא</term>. Cf.
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">פוריא</ref>
            </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft" facs="https://archive.org/details/GriechischeUndLateinischeLehnwrterInTalmudMidraschUndTargum/Griechische_und_lateinische_Lehnwrter2/page/n119/mode/2up">
                  <title>Krauss, LW II</title>
                  <citedRange>102b</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
